Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Most laboratory values are within normal limits. There is a mild elevation in hemoglobin and MCHC, which may suggest hemoconcentration or dehydration. Platelet distribution width is also elevated, possibly indicating increased platelet size variability, which can be seen in reactive states. No evidence of anemia, infection, or significant electrolyte or renal abnormalities. Clinical correlation is recommended.
